<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>My GAR system (Group Attack Range)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:17 p.m. 22/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> My GAR system (Group Attack Range)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1128" TARGET=_self>An Idea..</A> (Ragok)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>Read my earlier post on this about the GAR. I define a system that allows just what you suggested. The basis of the system is to take the highest level player in the group and subtract three from his level. Then divide his level by ten, round off, and again subtract this value from the total. This defines the minimum level allowed to group with this player. It also defines the range of players this group can attack, namely anyone that meets their GAR minimum and above the group can attack.
<P>Please refer to my original post a few pages back for the details.
<P>&gt; I had posted this a few days ago, but i doubt many people had
<BR>&gt; read my post so i will repost my idea.
<P>&gt; Mind you, this would need some experimenting with to see if it
<BR>&gt; is viable, but here goes:
<BR>&gt; The level difference for grouping is dynamic, meaning at higher
<BR>&gt; levels you can group with people more than the 5 level limit
<BR>&gt; everyone gets used to at lower levels, and satill gain
<BR>&gt; experience. The experience gain from defeating a monster
<BR>&gt; therefore is dynamic also, meaning at higher levels monsters con
<BR>&gt; at blue 3-4 levels lower, instead of just 1-2 like at lower
<BR>&gt; levels. I would like to see the 4 level limit for pvp be dynamic
<BR>&gt; also, meaning at level 30 you could go up against level 25's or
<BR>&gt; level 37's. The exact limits (or curve) in how the level limit
<BR>&gt; increases i am not sure of since i have no clue to the game code
<BR>&gt; itself (verant would need to do this since one would need to
<BR>&gt; understand the powercurve for levels).
<BR>&gt; Of course, as i stated above, this would need testing to see if
<BR>&gt; someone out of the 4 level limit at higher levels is too easy or
<BR>&gt; impossible to defeat in PvP. Also, this would only work if they
<BR>&gt; tweak the spell resistance that is currently in place.
<P>&gt; This i think is a must, since as people advance in levels, the
<BR>&gt; seperation (in levels) grows too since everyone advances at a
<BR>&gt; different rate. It then could lead to a shortage of victims (or
<BR>&gt; victimizers).
<P>&gt; Ragok Arnskull
<BR>&gt; skull@lvdi.net
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
